Giant Bubble Powder Concentrate, Works with Bubble Machines, Make Huge Bubbles with Our Mixture Just Add Dish Soap and Make Gigantic Bubbles Works for Normal Bubbles or Huge Bubbles
['Our bubble powder is a great summer-time goto for instant fun. Take our bubble powder, mix in some detergent and tap water, and you have hours of summer-time (huge bubble) fun. The recipe is simple, quick, and effective. You will be making huge professional bubbles that everyone in your neighborhood will be talking about. Kids are instantly impressed with these “awesome” bubbles and it’s a cinch to do.', "Hours of fun. This a great “science experiment” with a spectacular payoff, but you can even experiment with creating string wands. Just get two sticks from the yard and some string, create a bubble wand just like the pros. This is a great way to impress your kids and have a couple hours of really fun quality time. Kids love popping these humongous bubbles, they're instantly attracted to them.", 'Family Made. We’re a small family-owned company and bubble powder was a collective invention. We attended a parade with huge bubbles, and one of our children wanted to make them from home. WIth this, our bubble powder was born. There are some bubble recipes that do contain chemicals, so the goal was to make a bubble powder that was safe yet effective.', 'Food Grade Materials are all we use. Our bubble recipe is made from all food-grade supplies so it’s safe to be around and use. While we always recommend that an adult mixes the bubble powder, and ideally, you should use a kitchen mixer, all components in our recipe are made from food-grade only ingredients. You can rest easy that your handling safe materials, all sourced from the USA.', 'Made in the USA. We’re a small company based in the USA and all ingredients are food-grade and sourced within the USA.', 'Instructions for a gallon: 1 gallon of water, 1 slightly heaping teaspoon of bubble powder, 4 ounces - 8 ounces of dawn detergent (depending on humidity, start low and add more if you need to). Make HUGE bubbles if you can mix this with a kitchen handheld mixer. Make even bigger bubbles if you let this sit overnight. We recommend making 3 - 4 gallons and putting the liquid in a large 10 gallon bucket – this will last a very long time, likely months (in our personal experience).']
